# Proposals Module Rules

## Proposal Entity

Proposal from seller on buyer's request.

## Proposal Fields

- `id` - Unique identifier
- `requestId` - Request ID (foreign key to Request)
- `sellerId` - Seller ID (foreign key to User)
- `price` - Proposed price (UAH)
- `title` - Proposal title
- `description` - Detailed service description
- `estimatedTime` - Estimated completion time (1-2 days, week, etc.)
- `warranty` - Warranty (1 month, 3 months, etc.)
- `images` - Array of seller's work image URLs
- `status` - Status (pending, accepted, rejected, completed)

## Proposal Statuses

- `pending` - Awaiting buyer's decision
- `accepted` - Accepted by buyer
- `rejected` - Rejected by buyer
- `completed` - Deal completed

## Proposal Endpoints

- `GET /api/proposals/:id` - Get proposal details
- `POST /api/requests/:id/proposals` - Create proposal (seller only)
- `POST /api/proposals/:id/accept` - Accept proposal (buyer only)
- `POST /api/proposals/:id/reject` - Reject proposal (buyer only)
- `POST /api/proposals/:id/complete` - Complete deal (buyer only)
- `GET /api/proposals/:id/comments` - Get comments on proposal
- `POST /api/proposals/:id/comments` - Add comment to proposal

## Proposal Service

- Create proposal with status `pending`
- Award +5 XP to seller on creation
- Notify buyer when new proposal is created
- Handle proposal acceptance:
  - Update proposal status to `accepted`
  - Update request status to `closed`
  - Reject all other proposals for the request
  - Award +20 XP to buyer, +25 XP to seller
- Handle deal completion:
  - Update proposal status to `completed`
  - Update user statistics
  - Award +30 XP to buyer, +50 XP to seller

## Business Logic

1. **Creation:**
   - Seller creates proposal → status `pending`
   - Increment `proposalsCount` on request
   - Create notification for buyer

2. **Acceptance (transaction required):**
   - Update proposal status to `accepted`
   - Update request status to `closed`
   - Reject all other proposals
   - Award XP to both users
   - Create notifications

3. **Completion:**
   - Buyer marks deal as completed
   - Update user statistics
   - Award XP
   - Enable review option

## Validation

- Price: min 0
- Title: required, min 1 character
- Description: required, min 10 characters
- Estimated time: required
- Images: max 5 images
